  "response": "Yes, you can be arrested for downloading movies from torrents in India. Here's why:\n\n*   **Copyright Infringement:** Downloading copyrighted movies through torrents is considered copyright infringement under the Indian Copyright Act, 1957. Copyright holders have the exclusive right to reproduce, distribute, and communicate their work to the public. Downloading without permission violates these rights.\n\n*   **Penalties:**\n    *   **Imprisonment:** The Copyright Act provides for imprisonment ranging from six months to three years for copyright infringement.\n    *   **Fines:** Fines can range from \u20b950,000 to \u20b92,00,000.\n\n*   **Enforcement:** While not every single downloader gets caught, copyright holders and law enforcement agencies are actively pursuing and cracking down on piracy. They monitor torrent networks and can identify IP addresses of those downloading copyrighted material.\n\n*   **Distribution (Uploading):** It's important to note that torrenting involves both downloading and uploading. When you download a movie through a torrent, you're simultaneously uploading portions of it to other users. This makes you a distributor, which can lead to more severe penalties.\n\n*   **ISPs:** Internet Service Providers (ISPs) in India may be required to block access to websites hosting pirated content and may even be compelled to share information about subscribers engaged in illegal downloading activities.\n\n**In Summary:** Downloading movies through torrents in India is illegal due to copyright infringement. You risk facing legal consequences, including imprisonment and fines.\n",
